# Proposal

## What will (likely) be the title of your project?

Temple Run Inspired Game

## In just a sentence or two, summarize your project. (E.g., "A website that lets you buy and sell stocks.")

A simple running game similar to flash Run or Temple Run the mobile game.

## In a paragraph or more, detail your project. What will your software do? What features will it have? How will it be executed?

The software will be developed in C# within the unity game engine. It will have 3D graphical figures (such as the background and the path the player runs on) and measure the dietance the player runs. 
Running animations of the character, an active 3rd person camera, and (hopefullu) randomy generated paths will be implemented. It will feature a start menu and a game over screen. 

## If planning to combine 1051's final project with another course's final project, with which other course? And which aspect(s) of your proposed project would relate to 1051, and which aspect(s) would relate to the other course?

The basic coding strategies and knowledge that we have learned from 1051 will be implemented in creating the game as well as the skills we also have obtained in 1057 since much of unity uses c# to code.

