## In the world of software, most everything takes longer to implement than you expect. And so it's not uncommon to accomplish less in a fixed amount of time than you hope.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a GOOD outcome for your final project. I.e., what WILL you accomplish no matter what?

We hope to accomplish the basic background and foreground of the Temple Run inspired game, but we are unsure about the randomly generated paths that we wish to introduce. If all else fails, we have the option of creating the mods for the Binding of Issac Game that we spoke of on Thursday 4/6/23.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BETTER outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you THINK you can accomplish before the final project's deadline?

Definetly the mods, and the background for the Temple Run Game. 

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BEST outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you HOPE to accomplish before the final project's deadline?

We hope to accomplish a functioning, full fledge moc version of Temple Run that we described originally in the previous question. 

## In a paragraph or more, outline your next steps. What new skills will you need to acquire? What topics will you need to research? If working with one of two classmates, who will do what?

We plan on learning the basics of c# programming as well as the unity engine, modeling, and random generation in games. There are resources online via Youtube and Wikis that have already put together the first steps. We hope that this will be enough. 
